  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220&deg;C/ 200&deg;C (fan)/ 425&deg;F/ Gas 7</p>\r\n<p>Boil a kettle</p>\r\n<p>Slice the <strong>courgette<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong> into quarters lengthways and then chop into large bite-size pieces</p>\r\n<p>Trim the green stalks off the<strong> aubergine<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong> and chop&nbsp;into large, bite-size pieces</p>\r\n<p>Cut the <strong>chestnut mushrooms</strong> into quarters (or crumble them into rough pieces)</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1067.-step-1-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1067.-step-1-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1067.-step-1-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1067.-step-1-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1067.-step-1-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>chopped courgette</strong>, <strong>aubergine</strong> and <strong>mushrooms</strong> to a baking tray (use <strong>tin foil</strong> to avoid mess!) with a very generous drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong> and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong></p>\r\n<p>Put the tray in the oven for 20 min or until the vegetables are golden and tender</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1067.-step-2-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1067.-step-2-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1067.-step-2-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1067.-step-2-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1067.-step-2-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, peel and roughly dice the<strong> red onion<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong></p>\r\n<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a drizzle of<strong> olive oil</strong> over a medium heat</p>\r\n<p>Once hot, add the <strong>chopped onion</strong> with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and cook for 5-8 min or until beginning to soften and caramelise</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1067.-step-3-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1067.-step-3-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1067.-step-3-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1067.-step-3-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1067.-step-3-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, add the<strong> wheat berries</strong> to a pot with plenty of <strong>boiled water</strong> and&nbsp;1/2<span class=\"text-danger\"> [1]</span><strong> vegetable stock cube </strong>(you'll use the rest later!)</p>\r\n<p>Cook over a high heat for 12-15 min or until tender with a slight bite</p>\r\n<p>Once cooked, drain and return to the pot and leave to cool&nbsp;</p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
